    "content": "According to narrations, it is recommended to bathe oneself at the twenty-seventh night of Ramadan. It has been also narrated that Imam Ali ibn al-Husayn Zayn al-’Abidin (a.s.) used to repeat the following supplicatory prayer throughout this night:\r\n\r\n--اَللّٰهُمَّ ارْزُقْنِيْ التَّجَافِيْ عَنْ دَارِ الْغُرُوْرِ، وَالْاِنَابَةَ اِلٰى دَارِ الْخُلُوْدِ وَالْاِسْتِعْدَادَ لِلْمَوْتِ قَبْلَ حُلُوْلِ الْفَوْتِ۔", 
    "audio": "", 
    "transliteration": "", 
    "english": "According to narrations, it is recommended to bathe oneself at the twenty-seventh night of Ramadan. It has been also narrated that Imam Ali ibn al-Husayn Zayn al-’Abidin (a.s.) used to repeat the following supplicatory prayer throughout this night:\r\n\r\nO Allah, (please) present me alienation from the abode of delusion, turning to the abode of eternity, and readiness for death before it is too late."
}